parameters:
\nc<>Absolutely not! Don't give up, Sorbet. If you can endure
just a little longer, Levantia will come to help!
\nc<>Wait a moment, I'll do something about this right now...!

\nc<>What... is this? I thought I fought Candy, but why am I
still like this...?

\nc<>...No, right now, more importantly... Candy! Sorbet! Are
you okay?
\nc<>It's okay... Somehow, the barrier to keep people away...

\nc<>Not that! Shouldn't you be more concerned about your own
body?!

\nc<>(Ugh, such a terrible wound...) (Fortunately, it seems like
I can somehow manage with Candy's magic...)

\nc<>I'm sorry. Sorbet said they were going to call Kei-san. I
said we should try to handle it ourselves.

\nc<>(It's easy to say that everything will be fine here.) (From
now on, I'll support you in becoming even stronger.)
\nc<>(But, is that really for the sake of these children?)

\nc<>(First of all, it's wrong.) (If you look at the traces of
the barrier and the battle, you'll understand.)
\nc<>Candy and Sorbet are already respectable magical girls.

\nc<>(And yet, they're such a strong opponent that they got
injured this badly.)

\nc<>(Is it really the right choice to keep making these children
fight in such a situation...?)

\nc<>...You should understand too. Being a magical girl isn't
always just fun.
\nc<>There are plenty of difficult and painful things in life.

\nc<>So... I think it wouldn't be a bad idea to quit being a
magical girl and return to a normal life.

\nc<>(That's right. It's not too late even now.) (At least for
these children--)
\nc<>But, I don't intend to quit this job.

\nc<>Ah...! Why!? Even though we managed to get through this
time, there's no guarantee that I can help you next time!
\nc<>Yes, that's right. Honestly, I was really scared.

\nc<>If Kei-san hadn't come to help me in the end, I might have
been sitting down and crying by now.

\nc<>But... if I wasn't a magical girl, I wouldn't be able to
heal Lusha like this, right?
\nc<>I have to just silently watch Kei-san fight, right?
\nc<>I don't like it when it hurts and scares me.

\nc<>But, I hate just watching someone close to me being in pain
and scared even more.
\nc<>That's why I'm here right now, because I made up my mind.

\nc<>S-Stop it! It's because Lusha Sorbet became a magical girl
on her own, right!?
\nc<>Because magical girl outfits are cute. Cute is justice.
\nc<>Ah, don't move because the wound might spread!
\nc<>I see. Candy was thinking about it too.
\nc<>(...Why did I decide to become a magical girl again?)
\nc<>I obtained the memory K2: Why become a magical girl?.

\nc<>Good listeners increased by 7,000, while bad listeners
increased by 3,000.
